=09Chip Shot=20
=09=20
=09
=09There is so much information being pumped out this week surrounding the=
=20
Texas-Texas A=02?game, here is some of what both schools are releasing to t=
he=20
media in effort to bolster their team's image:=20
=09
=09 Texas A=02?is taking bragging rights over the 1990s after a 94-28-2 rec=
ord for=20
the decade. The Aggies won nine or more games eight times and 10 or more=20
games five times in the 1990s.=20
=09
=09 They are touting their 94 victories in the 1990s as more than any Texas=
=20
school in any single decade. The former record for wins in a decade was 88 =
by=20
Darrell Royal and Fred Akers' Texas teams in the 1970s.=20
=09
=09 Here's the list being promoted by the Aggies: 1. Texas A&M, 1990s, 94. =
2.=20
Texas, 1970s, 88. 3. Texas, 1960s, 86. 4. Texas Christian, 1930s, 83. 5.=20
Houston, 1970s, 80.=20
=09
=09 Texas fans, on the other hand, can probably take comfort in the only=20
statistic that matters concerning the Aggies: UT leads the overall series,=
=20
67-34-5.=20
