=09 Q: Looking at the haul of recruits Texas already has commitments from, =
is=20
there an area of need not being addressed? It appears that this is quite a=
=20
haul of offensive linemen, so it looks like a lot of redshirts in the makin=
g.=20
If he signs, what will Quan Cosby be asked to do? Doesn't he have a twin=20
brother - and is that a factor on where he signs? When all is said and done=
,=20
where do you think this class will rank come signing day in February and=20
which of the potential signees, not orally committed, will most determine=
=20
where that rank ends up? Also, with Sneezy Beltran coming off a redshirt ye=
ar=20
and from what I am reading, an impressive one at that, what do you see in t=
he=20
future for Cedric Benson? What about the returning RBs such as Ivan William=
s,=20
Kenny Hayter, et al? Is the abundance of talent at RB a good thing or too=
=20
much of a good thing? And one last thing: Is anyone looking to transfer aft=
er=20
the season?=20
=09?? Roy Cassas=20
=09
=09 BROWN:  Quarterbacks and linemen (on both sides of the ball) control th=
e=20
game, so you can never have enough of those positions. UT is filling its=20
needs nicely with the commitments that it has. The player that can probably=
=20
make the biggest difference is Tommie Harris of Killeen Ellison, perhaps th=
e=20
best defensive tackle in the country. UT's class is shaping up as a top 10=
=20
nationally, again. If Harris comes, it will climb. But as is the case with=
=20
all of this recruiting hype, it's just that - hype. Who knows if Cedric=20
Benson will play next year? He has to come down here in the heat of August=
=20
and prove to the coaches that he's better than Kenny Hayter, Ivan Williams,=
=20
Victor Ike and Sneezy Beltran. I would say Benson's chances are good if som=
e=20
of those guys don't toughen up and let loose. But time will tell. As far as=
=20
guys looking to transfer, there aren't any rumblings yet. Stay tuned.=20
